{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe auto-lander needs an opt-in, machine-readable \"please land this\" intent that agents set and the bot consumes as a lease. Under Fast-Forward-Only `main` (ADR-0040) the label must be **non-gating** (FFO already enforces up-to-date, so gating would be redundant and add a wedge) and **non-sticky** (it is about the current tip). Research (GerriScary/CVE-2025-1568) requires a tight vote ACL.\n\n> **Name collision:** `Autosubmit` must be a **project-authored label**, NOT Gerrit's first-party `autosubmit` submit-plugin (lowercase) — the plugin auto-submits on gate satisfaction, which is not what we want. Author our own label.\n\n## What\nAuthor an `Autosubmit` Gerrit label in `infra/gerrit/project.config` and apply it to live `refs/meta/config` (operator cutover — detect-only under ADR-0026). Vote ACL granted to **Contributors (requesters)** so an agent can set the label under its OWN Gerrit identity (S4's `land`). ACL line: `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] label-Autosubmit = -1..+1 group Contributors`. `function = NoBlock`; empty `copyCondition`. Setting the label only REQUESTS a land (non-gating); the bot still requires `is:submittable` (both real votes MAX) and re-verifies at submit, so a requester-votable ACL is not a security vector. **This canonical account/group naming is what the epic and downstream stories reference.**\n\n## Scope\nConfig + ACL + cutover ONLY. The service that reads the label is a separate story.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `Autosubmit` label added to `infra/gerrit/project.config` with `-1..+1`, `function = NoBlock`, empty `copyCondition` (drops on every new patchset), and explicit value lines: `value = 0 No score`, `value = +1 Land this change`, and `value = -1 Do not land` (the `-1..+1` range is fixed, so all three value lines are required — the `-1` line is NOT optional).\n- [ ] `label-Autosubmit` vote ACL granted to group `Contributors` (requesters) + Administrators via `[access \"refs/heads/*\"] label-Autosubmit = -1..+1 group Contributors`, so an agent can request a land under its own identity; `addPatchSet` cannot forge it (empty `copyCondition` drops it on every new patchset).\n- [ ] Label is NOT referenced by any submit requirement (non-gating; FFO enforces up-to-date structurally).\n- [ ] `config-check` passes; live cutover applied to `refs/meta/config` and verified via `GET /projects/rebar/labels/Autosubmit`.\n- [ ] **Security-invariants artifact:** the ADR-0042 Security invariants section records the \"non-gating label + bot re-verifies the two-vote gate on the exact tested SHA at submit\" invariant (the protection is the re-verify at submit, NOT restricting who may set `Autosubmit`) with its concrete checks — a `grep` of `infra/gerrit/project.config` proving `function = NoBlock` / no submit-requirement reference, and that the bot only submits when `is:submittable` holds on the tested SHA — demonstrating the label cannot weaken the two-vote (`LLM-Review`+`Verified`) gate."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783743836550943001,"uuid":"89ddf731-4804-44a3-b63a-4992f9e44c25"}